        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Buying gold jewellery is not just an emotional decision—it’s also a financial investment. In India, where gold holds cultural and monetary value, ensuring its authenticity is extremely important. This is where gold hallmarking comes into play.</p><p>A hallmark is a certification that guarantees the purity of gold. In India, this is regulated by the BIS (Bureau of Indian Standards). Here are 10 simple and practical ways to verify gold hallmarks in India, explained with real-life examples.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_3pECG9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1. Check for the BIS Hallmark Logo",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>1. Check for the BIS Hallmark Logo</h2>",
            "custom_id": "check",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_CEdw84": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Check_for_the_BIS_Hallmark_Logo.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The first and most important sign is the BIS logo stamped on the jewellery.</p><p>What to look for: A triangular BIS logo engraved on the piece.</p><p>Real-life example: You’re buying a gold ring at a jewellery store. Before paying, you check inside the band and spot a small triangle symbol—that confirms BIS certification.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_C4KUKT": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image With Text ",
          "settings": {
